*GRUB Legacy

[A] key
append options to the kernel boot line

[C] key
open up the GRUB command line

[ESC] key
escapes out of any GRUB menu

Arrow Keys
Used to highlight an option in the GRUB menu

*GRUB2

[E] key
used to edit a GRUB menu item

[ESC] key to go to previous menu item

Cntrl+x or F10
boots a selection or modified line

